post_text:
The sharks were circling but they were no match for our
@DanielMorganTechnologyCenter students from SHS!

Ms. Rogers's students competed in a "Shark Tank" style competition on Friday. Student groups created original products and services to help others and pitched them to a panel of "Sharks". Spartanburg High School freshmen Ajyia Wright, Jada Steen, and Ashlon Fields (pictured) took first place with their service called "Good Vibe," which is designed to help fellow students deal with cyber bullying. #DMTCPrepares #ToInspireAndEquip

